DML
----
DML (Data Manipulation Language) is used to work with the data
inside tables — inserting, updating, deleting, and retrieving records.


-------
INSERT
-------
insert (add data)

insert into table (column1,column2,column3)
values (value1, value2, value3);

-------
UPDATE
-------
update table_name
set column_name=value,column_name=value
where condition;

Note : Without WHERE, all rows will be updated


------
delete
-------

delete form table_name
where condition;



Key Points (Interview Important)
----------------------------------
DML deals with data, not structure
Changes can be rolled back (unlike DDL in many cases)
Uses transactions (COMMIT, ROLLBACK)


